com.dg.libs.rest.callbacks

Interface HttpCallback<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Parameter that indicates which object the callback returns. It can be of any type.

    public interface HttpCallback<T>
    The HttpCallback interface is used for HTTP request notification. It contains methods that describe the error if the callback fails and return response data if the callback succeeds.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onHttpError(ResponseStatus responseStatus)
      This method shows that the callback has failed due to server issue, no connectivity or parser error
      void onSuccess(T responseData, ResponseStatus responseStatus)
      This method shows that the callback successfully finished.
